\begin_layout Standard
Long ago, Songwrite 3 was called Songwrite 2, Songwrite 1 and even GTablature.
 Here are the various versions in a chronological order:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
GTablature was the first version of a tablature editor, written with Python
 and Gtk.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Songwrite 1 was a rewrite of GTablature using Tk instead of Gtk.
 In fact, switching from Gtk to Gtk 2 was a pain, and thePython Gtk API
 was instable.
 This version also introduced the use of EditObj 1 for generating dialog
 boxes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Songwrite 2 is a full rewrite of Songwrite 1, still in Python but with a
 new interface based on Gtk 2 and Cairo.
 It seems that Python Gtk2 API has improved in the while! Songwrite 3 uses
 now EditObj 2, my new dialog box automatic generator, and it also has a
 new plugin systems.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Songwrite 3 is a full rewrite of Songwrite 2, in Python 3 and Qt.
 Qt now replaces Gtk; I finally come to appreciate Gtk 2 but version 3 is
 even worst, from a programmer point of view but also from a user point
 of view.
\end_layout

